description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an ambitious Medical Director to provide senior leadership to our medical and dental workforce and associated corporate support services. The role requires a registered Dentist (as per the Dentists Act 1984) or GMC registered doctor or who may currently be a consultant in a secondary care specialty, a GP, consultant psychiatrist or consultant in public health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Director will be responsible for clinical leadership, building, motivating and developing clinicians within Bridgewater in partnership with our Chief Nurse and for leading on clinical service strategy in a multi-organisational, integrated care context. Crucial to the role will be the requirement to develop and enhance clinical relationships with CCGs, GPs, NHS provider partners and public health colleagues in Local Authorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Director will work closely with the Trust’s Chief Nurse to continually improve quality, clinical outcomes and patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Board, the Medical Director will hold corporate responsibility jointly with other Board members for the strategic direction, corporate policy making and development and delivery of the organisation’s objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful you will join the Trust at an exciting time in our development. We are focusing on the implementation of our Quality &amp; Place Strategy, including the integration of health and social care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is and will continue to respond innovatively to the Five Year Forward View and our commissioners’ plans, as well as our own clinicians’ ambitions for their services. The passion we all share at Bridgewater is to deliver resilient health and care services in partnership with others whether they be in the NHS, the wider public sector, the third sector or in business - improving health, adding social value and building upon the assets of our citizens and their communities. Our challenge is to develop service and financial models that improve our ability to deliver cost effective excellent care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Director of the Trust, you will support the delivery of our strategic objectives which prioritise supporting our staff to achieve a capable, caring, well led workforce, and along with other leaders you will act as a role model in living the Trust’s values, promoting compassionate leadership behaviours and helping make the Trust a great place to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for ensuring that innovative and up-to-date practices are in place to provide the very best support to colleagues across the Trust and to enable the delivery of high quality care, whilst ensuring that legal and statutory requirements are met and that resources are used prudentl&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fit &amp; Proper Persons Test (Directors)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provider organisations must ensure that they only employ individuals who are fit for their role and are required to assess the fitness of such nominated individuals. Director posts will be subject to the requirements of Regulation 5 of the Health &amp; Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) Regulations 2014. A Self-Declaration Form will be completed, alongside various employment checks, including a review of the Insolvency Register and Disqualified Directors Register.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please ensure that you read the Job Description which also includes the person specification before applying for this post.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal chat or further information regarding this post please contact debra.harrop@nhs.net who will arrange contact with &lt;strong&gt;Lynne Carter – Deputy Chief Executive &amp; Chief Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date for applications: 9th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: To be confirmed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the current situation with COVID-19 we will look to support all successful applicants’ needs during the interview process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the advertised post requires a DBS check the successful candidate will incur the cost of the DBS check which will be taken in three equal monthly instalments from salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We advise that you complete and submit your application form as soon as possible, because should we experience a high level of interest in the post it may be closed early.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Any applicant who applies for a position online will be contacted thereafter using the email address provided upon login. Please ensure that after application you check your emails often to ensure that you do not miss any communications from Bridgewater Community Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bridgewater is an equal opportunities employer: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value and respect the diversity of our employees and aim to recruit a workforce that reflects our local communities, we therefore welcome applications from everyone with the necessary attributes for the job, irrespective of age, disability, gender/gender identity, sexual orientation, ethnicity, religious belief or other personal circumstance. We are committed to improving the working lives of our employees and we have an active flexible working policy and welcome applications for job share, part-time and flexible working. An interview is guaranteed to any applicant with a disability who meets the essential criteria of the person specification. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the application process please contact the Recruiting Manager for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
